<i>Posted by Phyleus on 06-03-02 02:47 AM:</i>

<p><b> </b></p>

<p>Ok.. here's the deal...<br />
<br />
<br />
Like Greg, I have big plans a brewing for Akalabethians in DAoC.  Once I figure out my work schedule, I'm going to have a guild group night, set for every week at a scheduled time.  <br />
<br />
I like to call it <font color="red">Phy Nigh</font> <br />
<br />
Every week it's going to be something different. But it will not include RvR.  Greggar is going to set that stuff up so he'll try to be an "unofficial" external event person and I'll try to be the "unofficial" internal event guy.  <br />
<br />
What kind of events eh?  It's gonna be stuff where we all will get to know each other... maybe not in the same night, but eventually.  One night might be powerleveling level 20's night, where I'll need one or two level 40's (or Chao or Solf), where we fight stuff red/low purple to us and let the lowbies reap the benefits.  Another night might be a Llyn Barfog Raid night or a Darkness Falls night.  So we might not all be able to go on an XP/Loot raid (because it's too dangerous), but they'll be times where we will be able to go together.  <br />
<br />
The times when we ALL will be together is the RvR nights that Greggar is going to set up.  EVERYONE is welcome... and hopefully expected to come if possible... to this event.  RvR can be awesome some nights.. and be horrible others, but at least we'll be doing it together, and we'll all be there.<br />
<br />
The reason for this of course is to level up but more so.. to get to know each other better.  For those of us who have to read what happens at gatherings for some reason or another instead of being there, this is where we'll learn about each other and what we do.  So yeah... the conversation will be a little bit more on a personal level, but I think that's one of the great things about our guild... we don't just hide behind our "cover names".. we care about the person behind it (and their families too).<br />
<br />
So.... when will it start? Not sure... I'm thinking on Tuesday's or Wednesdays about 8 central.. but like I said.. gotta figure out my work schedule.  But this is and WILL happen.  I'll post the event on the boards most likely the Sunday before it happens, and will have a signup, first come first serve, for the number and levels we need.  This is a GUILD event and such, they'll be events we can do by ourselves or VERY close friends of the guild.  <br />
<br />
If you have any questions or comments, post 'em here, and don't forget to comment on Greg's ideas.<br />
<br />
Phyleus</p>
